Money Stuff =0A In the spring of 2022, Elon Musk offered to buy Twitter Inc=
. for about $44 =0Abillion. Twitter=E2=80=99s board of directors met with =
its investment ban =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=
=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12581725&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525=
&p=3D02112025>=0A=0A=0A=0AOpenAI hostile takeover=0A=0AIn the spring of 202=
2, Elon Musk offered to buy <> Twitter Inc. for about $44 =0Abillion. Twitt=
er=E2=80=99s board of directors met with its investment bankers to =0Adiscu=
ss exactly one question: Was Musk=E2=80=99s offer more than Twitter was wor=
th =0Aotherwise (on its own or in a competing deal)=3F The bankers and boar=
d concluded =0Athat Twitter was not going to do better for its shareholders=
 than Musk was =0Aoffering, so they took Musk=E2=80=99s deal.=0A=0AA lot of=
 Twitter employees and users were sad about this. Musk=E2=80=99s takeover w=
as, =0Alet=E2=80=99s say, a mixed bag for Twitter=E2=80=99s employees and u=
sers and advertisers, and =0Afor its role in public life. At the time, the =
